tags: ["PYQ", "NEET PG 2024"],
text: "At what pressure is the pop-up valve released in bag and mask ventilation?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "30-40 cm of H\u2082O", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "40-50 cm of H\u2082O", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "50-60 cm of H\u2082O", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "60-70 cm of H\u2082O", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "In bag-and-mask ventilation, the **pop-off (pressure-release) valve opens at 30\u201340 cm H\u2082O** to prevent barotrauma.<br><br>This protects the neonatal lungs from excessive pressure during positive-pressure ventilation.<br><br>The valve can be overridden only in special situations like severe lung stiffness.",
