text: "A newly renovated operating theatre is having essential anesthesia equipment installed. During routine inspection of the anesthesia workstation, the technician suddenly develops lightheadedness and nausea. He immediately switches off the anesthesia machine and leaves the room. Which of the following is the most likely cause of his symptoms?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Leakage of Isoflurane", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Leakage of Halothane", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Leakage of Nitrous Oxide", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "D", "text": "Leakage of Sevoflurane", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "Nitrous oxide exposure causes:<br><br>* dizziness\n* nausea\n* euphoria / disorientation\n* headache\n* diffusion hypoxia (with sudden discontinuation)<br><br>It is also the most common anesthetic gas associated with chronic occupational exposure issues, especially in poorly scavenged OTs.",
