explanation: "The cuff of a tracheostomy tube forms a seal against the tracheal wall, primarily **preventing air leakage during ventilation and reducing the risk of aspiration**. This ensures effective delivery of positive-pressure ventilation while protecting the airway from oropharyngeal secretions.",
