explanation: "The image depicts the **sniffing position**, where the neck is flexed and the head is extended at the atlanto-occipital joint. This alignment brings the oral, pharyngeal, and laryngeal axes into a more favourable line, making it the standard and most effective position for endotracheal intubation.",
