explanation: "A nasopharyngeal airway is a soft, flexible tube inserted through the nostril to maintain airway patency, especially in conscious or semi-conscious patients who cannot tolerate an oropharyngeal airway. Its bevelled tip and flared end distinguish it from other airway adjuncts.\n<img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/0190d16e-2847-42c4-bc72-bedee3ba59da.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
